1
00:00:04,830 --> 00:00:07,230
Lisanna, where are you?

2
00:00:07,570 --> 00:00:09,420
Hey, answer me!

3
00:00:09,420 --> 00:00:10,700
Lisanna!

4
00:00:12,960 --> 00:00:14,460
Oww...

5
00:00:14,460 --> 00:00:15,560
Damn it...

6
00:00:18,840 --> 00:00:20,120
Lisanna!

7
00:01:59,830 --> 00:02:01,760
What is it?

8
00:02:02,260 --> 00:02:03,850
Just a dream...?

9
00:02:03,850 --> 00:02:07,260
What are you doing making such an 
insinuating face in someone else's house?

10
00:02:08,070 --> 00:02:12,440
Since you took the bed, I ended 
up sleeping on the floor!

11
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:15,190
Man, so noisy right when I wake up...

12
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:20,110
This, coming from someone who just had a 
sleepover at my house without permission?

13
00:02:20,110 --> 00:02:24,370
I can't help it, man! I get 
the best sleep in this bed.

14
00:02:24,370 --> 00:02:25,070
Aye!

15
00:02:25,070 --> 00:02:27,180
Then why don't you buy your own?

16
00:02:27,180 --> 00:02:28,770
Well, I'm hungry.

17
00:02:28,770 --> 00:02:29,510
Aye.

18
00:02:29,510 --> 00:02:31,250
So, what was the dream about?

19
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:34,610
You woke up from a dream, right?

20
00:02:37,150 --> 00:02:39,370
Right then, let's get some grub!

21
00:02:39,370 --> 00:02:40,360
Aye, sir!

22
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,390
Don't dodge the question!

23
00:02:43,940 --> 00:02:45,280
Gildarts!

24
00:02:49,810 --> 00:02:53,530
Looks like both Carla and you, Wendy, 
have gotten used to the guild.

25
00:02:53,530 --> 00:02:54,340
Yes!

26
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:56,740
She's especially glad about the women's dorm.

27
00:02:56,740 --> 00:03:00,210
By the way, why aren't you 
in the dorm, Lucy-san?

28
00:03:00,210 --> 00:03:03,480
I only found out about the 
women's dorm recently.

29
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:06,990
And it turned out the rent in 
the dorm is 100,000 jewel...

30
00:03:06,990 --> 00:03:10,150
If I'd gotten a place there, I wouldn't 
be able to pay that much lately.

31
00:03:11,710 --> 00:03:13,500
Big news!

32
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:24,170
What is it?

33
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:25,970
The bells are ringing?

34
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:28,240
Them ringing like this means...

35
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:28,890
Aye!

36
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:31,230
Could it be?

37
00:03:31,230 --> 00:03:32,360
Those bells...

38
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,300
Here we go!

39
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:33,980
It's him, right?

40
00:03:34,460 --> 00:03:36,770
Gildarts has come back!

41
00:03:36,770 --> 00:03:37,940
Aye, sir!

42
00:03:37,940 --> 00:03:40,690
Gildarts!

43
00:03:40,690 --> 00:03:46,210
Gildarts? I've never met him. Who is he?

44
00:03:46,210 --> 00:03:48,820
He's Fairy Tail's strongest wizard.

45
00:03:49,810 --> 00:03:52,960
Wait, even stronger than Erza?

46
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:55,550
I'm not even in his league.

47
00:03:56,090 --> 00:03:58,130
How dangerous can this guy get?

48
00:04:00,630 --> 00:04:04,120
Not like I care, but what's 
the celebration about?

49
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:06,440
It's like a festival, Carla!

50
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:08,710
Definitely one festive guild...

51
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:11,010
It's only natural for everyone to celebrate.

52
00:04:11,010 --> 00:04:13,520
It's been about three 
years since he came back.

53
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:16,860
Three years? What was he doing?

54
00:04:17,370 --> 00:04:22,010
There are quests more difficult 
than S class, called SS class.

55
00:04:22,010 --> 00:04:26,240
But there are jobs even above 
those, called ten-year quests.

56
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:28,450
Ten-year quests?

57
00:04:29,330 --> 00:04:32,680
No one has completed them 
for more than ten years.

58
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:34,410
That's why they're called ten-year quests.

59
00:04:34,890 --> 00:04:39,550
Gildarts went on one even more 
difficult, a hundred-year quest.

60
00:04:39,550 --> 00:04:41,300
Hundred-year quest?

61
00:04:41,540 --> 00:04:44,790
No one has managed to complete 
it for a hundred years?!

62
00:04:44,790 --> 00:04:45,680
Right.

63
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:47,290
It's Gildarts!

64
00:04:47,290 --> 00:04:49,220
Gildarts has returned!

65
00:04:49,220 --> 00:04:51,600
Magnolia will now change to Gildarts Shift!

66
00:04:51,850 --> 00:04:55,570
Residents, please move 
to the designated areas!

67
00:04:55,570 --> 00:04:58,330
Even so, isn't this going a bit overboard?

68
00:04:58,330 --> 00:04:59,310
I wonder...

69
00:04:59,310 --> 00:05:03,060
What is Magnolia's "Gildarts Shift"?

70
00:05:03,060 --> 00:05:04,900
You'll know if you look outside.

71
00:05:13,670 --> 00:05:14,740
Whoa!

72
00:05:14,740 --> 00:05:16,290
What is this?

73
00:05:29,910 --> 00:05:32,850
The city is... splitting!

74
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:36,140
Gildarts uses Crash Magic.

75
00:05:36,140 --> 00:05:38,300
He'll turn anything he touches into bits...

76
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:41,640
If his mind wanders, he'll just walk 
straight through people's houses.

77
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:43,190
How much of an idiot is he?

78
00:05:43,190 --> 00:05:46,050
So, the entire city was 
reconstructed with this in mind?!

79
00:05:46,050 --> 00:05:47,900
That's amazing! Isn't it, Carla?

80
00:05:47,900 --> 00:05:49,910
Yes. Amazingly stupid.

81
00:05:53,010 --> 00:05:54,330
He's coming!

82
00:05:54,330 --> 00:05:55,340
Aye!

83
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:22,410
Gildarts, fight me!

84
00:06:22,410 --> 00:06:23,980
Right off the bat with that?!

85
00:06:23,980 --> 00:06:25,130
Welcome back.

86
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:27,370
So, this person is Gildarts...

87
00:06:28,290 --> 00:06:33,570
Miss, I was pretty sure there was a 
guild named Fairy Tail around here...

88
00:06:33,570 --> 00:06:36,830
This is it. Oh, and I'm Mirajane.

89
00:06:37,860 --> 00:06:38,830
Mira?

90
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:43,670
Oh! You've really changed!

91
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:46,520
And wow, the guild is brand-new!

92
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:48,630
He didn't notice from the outside?

93
00:06:48,630 --> 00:06:50,270
Gildarts!

94
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:53,410
Natsu, is it? Been a while!

95
00:06:54,780 --> 00:06:58,660
I told you to fight me!

96
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:02,600
Maybe another time.

97
00:07:07,340 --> 00:07:10,350
I knew it! He's crazy strong!

98
00:07:10,350 --> 00:07:12,460
You ain't changed a bit, Pops.

99
00:07:12,460 --> 00:07:14,470
A Man among Men!

100
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:18,010
There are faces I never seen before...

101
00:07:18,010 --> 00:07:19,940
Things sure have changed...

102
00:07:20,340 --> 00:07:22,000
Gildarts!

103
00:07:22,410 --> 00:07:25,360
Oh, Master! Long time no see.

104
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:27,140
How did the job go?

105
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:38,560
No good. It's impossible for me.

106
00:07:40,190 --> 00:07:41,100
You've got to be kidding me!

107
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:42,270
The one and only Gildarts...

108
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:43,320
...failed a quest?

109
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:44,100
I can't believe it!

110
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:48,070
Even Pops couldn't handle it?

111
00:07:49,420 --> 00:07:51,570
Knowing when to withdraw is also being a Man!

112
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:55,700
Impossible, even for Fairy 
Tail's strongest wizard?

113
00:07:56,110 --> 00:07:59,090
What in the world is this hundred-year quest?

114
00:07:59,570 --> 00:08:02,010
You aren't ready for a hundred-year quest.

115
00:08:02,330 --> 00:08:03,440
Don't even consider it.

116
00:08:04,410 --> 00:08:06,580
Do I look rarin' to go to you?

117
00:08:06,580 --> 00:08:09,650
I see. Even you couldn't handle it?

118
00:08:09,650 --> 00:08:12,530
Sorry, this'll be bad for our reputation.

119
00:08:12,530 --> 00:08:15,550
No, I'm just happy you 
came back safe and sound.

120
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:21,220
You're the first one I know that's 
ever come back from this quest alive.

121
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:26,530
I wanna get some rest, so I'm heading home.

122
00:08:27,230 --> 00:08:29,880
Man, I'm beat...

123
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:31,220
Natsu!

124
00:08:32,270 --> 00:08:35,160
Come to my place later. 
I've brought souvenirs!

125
00:08:38,620 --> 00:08:40,200
Now, pardon me.

126
00:08:45,570 --> 00:08:46,730
My, my...

127
00:08:46,730 --> 00:08:48,470
Use the door, man!

128
00:08:49,530 --> 00:08:51,520
I wonder what he brought me?

129
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,440
I can't wait!

130
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:56,230
Don't go copying him!

131
00:08:56,630 --> 00:08:57,470
My, my...

132
00:08:58,020 --> 00:09:00,140
Happy, let's hurry up and go!

133
00:09:02,170 --> 00:09:06,270
Hey... Are Gildarts and 
Natsu really that close?

134
00:09:06,270 --> 00:09:09,710
Aye! The difference in their 
skills are like night and day,

135
00:09:09,710 --> 00:09:12,610
but it seems like Gildarts 
has taken a liking to Natsu.

136
00:09:14,350 --> 00:09:17,770
But Gildarts only comes back 
once in a while, right?

137
00:09:17,770 --> 00:09:22,560
Aye! He came back right after I was born...

138
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,790
Still no fish?

139
00:09:27,790 --> 00:09:30,960
I'm gonna catch you a big 
one soon, so just wait!

140
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:33,130
But we've hardly had any bites...

141
00:09:33,130 --> 00:09:36,670
Oh, right... Lisanna was with us back then.

142
00:09:38,180 --> 00:09:39,160
Hooked one!

143
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:40,050
You can do it!

144
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:43,280
Alright!

145
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:44,560
Tiny...

146
00:09:45,980 --> 00:09:47,250
Well, it is what it is!

147
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:50,650
Weren't you going to catch me a big one?

148
00:09:50,650 --> 00:09:53,770
I know! You'll get one, just wait!

149
00:09:55,970 --> 00:09:59,420
It's like you're the dad 
getting angry at his son.

150
00:09:59,420 --> 00:10:01,370
Why am I the dad?

151
00:10:01,370 --> 00:10:03,920
I don't want a dad like that!

152
00:10:04,340 --> 00:10:07,440
But you see, since I'm your wife, Natsu...

153
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,920
This again?

154
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:10,670
I never gave my permission for that!

155
00:10:10,670 --> 00:10:12,380
Aw, you're blushing again!

156
00:10:12,380 --> 00:10:14,700
It'll be true soon enough!

157
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:16,420
Shut up, you little brat!

158
00:10:16,420 --> 00:10:18,850
You're so cute when you're embarrassed!

159
00:10:19,970 --> 00:10:22,230
She lllikes you!

160
00:10:22,230 --> 00:10:24,060
Stop rolling your tongue like that!

161
00:10:32,090 --> 00:10:36,330
Natsu, do you remember 
your mom or dad's face?

162
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:44,200
For me, Mira-nee and Elf-nii are 
so kind, I don't feel lonely.

163
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:48,480
But I don't know what it's like 
to feel the warmth of parents...

164
00:10:49,430 --> 00:10:51,160
Warmth?

165
00:10:51,430 --> 00:10:53,200
You know what it's like, Natsu?

166
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:54,380
Not sure...

167
00:10:54,810 --> 00:10:57,690
But I know about Igneel's warmth.

168
00:10:57,690 --> 00:10:59,130
Igneel's?

169
00:11:00,410 --> 00:11:01,640
I see...

170
00:11:03,550 --> 00:11:04,860
Igneel...

171
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:08,700
Why did you leave me behind?

172
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:12,640
I searched all over for you!

173
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:16,640
And yet, you were nowhere to be found...

174
00:11:17,620 --> 00:11:18,490
I...

175
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:20,470
Natsu...

176
00:11:22,910 --> 00:11:27,270
Now that you mention it, I saw some huge 
footprints on the outskirts of East Forest.

177
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:28,710
Whoa, for real?

178
00:11:28,710 --> 00:11:32,620
Yup! Although I can't guarantee it 
was from a dragon or anything...

179
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:34,980
Alright, let's go! Right now!

180
00:11:34,980 --> 00:11:37,090
But, the sun will set soon...

181
00:11:37,090 --> 00:11:38,800
It don't matter!

182
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,530
I'll go myself!

183
00:11:40,530 --> 00:11:42,100
Tell me where they are!

184
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,800
What is it, Natsu?

185
00:11:44,780 --> 00:11:48,010
Okay, I understand. Let's go together.

186
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:51,590
All right! I'm gettin' fired up!

187
00:12:02,340 --> 00:12:04,320
Hey, I'm scared...

188
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:07,380
It'll be fine! Lisanna, are they there?

189
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:10,950
I was pretty sure it was near here, but...

190
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:13,490
There they are!

191
00:12:13,990 --> 00:12:15,780
These are footprints?

192
00:12:15,780 --> 00:12:16,960
They're really big!

193
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,230
What do you think, Natsu?

194
00:12:20,370 --> 00:12:22,670
I think this is from a forest Vulcan.

195
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:28,240
Forest Vulcan... You mean a Gorian 
like you fought with that other time?

196
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:33,260
Yeah...

197
00:12:33,260 --> 00:12:39,090
Igneel's not just going to show up so 
close after I searched for him so hard.

198
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:44,110
I'm sorry... My mistake got 
your hopes up, didn't it?

199
00:12:44,380 --> 00:12:46,370
It's okay, don't worry 'bout it.

200
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:48,230
Now, let's go home.

201
00:12:56,590 --> 00:12:59,710
Where are you, Igneel?

202
00:13:00,660 --> 00:13:03,120
Natsu, hold up!

203
00:13:04,290 --> 00:13:07,870
W-Walk a little slower, would you?

204
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:09,060
Sorry, my bad...

205
00:13:16,160 --> 00:13:18,230
It's gotten foggy...

206
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:23,710
Natsu, shouldn't we wait for Lisanna?

207
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:27,800
Lisanna, hurry up!

208
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:30,820
Wait... Where'd Lisanna go?

209
00:13:30,820 --> 00:13:33,650
See why I said to wait?

210
00:13:33,650 --> 00:13:38,470
Crap... If they find out she 
got lost, even for a second...

211
00:13:38,470 --> 00:13:40,080
That's terrible of you, Natsu.

212
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:42,870
Get ready to cry, 'cause 
you're in for a beating!

213
00:13:42,870 --> 00:13:45,920
You were slacking off! But it's nothing 
a good beating can't straighten out!

214
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:47,430
Lisanna!

215
00:13:47,430 --> 00:13:48,720
Hey!

216
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:50,220
Lisanna!

217
00:13:50,220 --> 00:13:52,220
Come here!

218
00:13:52,220 --> 00:13:55,130
Hey, answer me, Lisanna!

219
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:58,940
Oww...

220
00:13:58,940 --> 00:14:00,240
Damn it.

221
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,150
There it is!

222
00:14:07,150 --> 00:14:09,510
Long time no see, brat!

223
00:14:09,510 --> 00:14:11,830
Looking for this?

224
00:14:11,830 --> 00:14:12,840
Natsu!

225
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:13,900
Lisanna!

226
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:16,610
Let Lisanna go, you dumb ape!

227
00:14:16,610 --> 00:14:18,110
No!

228
00:14:18,110 --> 00:14:22,740
I picked it up, so it's mine! No returns!

229
00:14:22,740 --> 00:14:24,560
Lisanna isn't an object!

230
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:25,650
That's right!

231
00:14:25,650 --> 00:14:29,910
Since you're mine, how about you be my wife?

232
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:33,930
N-No...

233
00:14:35,110 --> 00:14:36,720
I can't see it...

234
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:39,890
I know! This is called "forbidden love"!

235
00:14:39,890 --> 00:14:45,110
I'm going to be Natsu's wife, 
so I can't go out with you.

236
00:14:46,980 --> 00:14:49,590
In that case, I'm <i>really </i>
not going to give you back!

237
00:14:49,980 --> 00:14:51,490
Say that again, you...

238
00:14:51,490 --> 00:14:55,010
You bullied me, so I won't give her back!

239
00:14:55,010 --> 00:14:57,950
If you insist I return her, then apologize!

240
00:14:57,950 --> 00:14:59,330
Why should I do that?

241
00:15:00,780 --> 00:15:02,170
Don't do it, Natsu!

242
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:08,400
What's the matter? You get down on your 
knees and I'll give her right back.

243
00:15:09,830 --> 00:15:11,290
Have it your way.

244
00:15:11,950 --> 00:15:13,390
Natsu...

245
00:15:16,030 --> 00:15:18,580
Sorry, I was wrong back then.

246
00:15:18,580 --> 00:15:21,690
So, give Lisanna back!

247
00:15:21,690 --> 00:15:22,770
Natsu...

248
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,980
No ways!

249
00:15:27,670 --> 00:15:28,810
Hey!

250
00:15:28,810 --> 00:15:29,900
What are you doing?

251
00:15:31,290 --> 00:15:33,350
You fell for it!

252
00:15:34,430 --> 00:15:36,370
Damn you...

253
00:15:37,190 --> 00:15:39,030
I feel much better now.

254
00:15:39,310 --> 00:15:42,160
Therefore it's time to finish you off!

255
00:15:48,670 --> 00:15:51,300
You're a very dangerous monkey.

256
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:52,550
Gildarts!

257
00:15:52,550 --> 00:15:55,420
Who are you?

258
00:15:55,420 --> 00:15:56,760
Get out of here.

259
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:02,850
Put down the girl, and leave this forest.

260
00:16:03,260 --> 00:16:05,960
Never come back here again.

261
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:09,030
Right! Apologies!

262
00:16:09,030 --> 00:16:09,950
Thank you!

263
00:16:10,370 --> 00:16:12,620
What was your name again?

264
00:16:12,620 --> 00:16:14,190
I'm Lisanna.

265
00:16:14,190 --> 00:16:16,620
Right... Mira's little sister.

266
00:16:17,230 --> 00:16:19,560
Natsu, are you okay?

267
00:16:19,560 --> 00:16:20,460
Yeah...

268
00:16:21,580 --> 00:16:23,910
Whoa! A cat's got wings!

269
00:16:23,910 --> 00:16:25,750
His name is Happy!

270
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:28,990
Gildarts, I...

271
00:16:29,490 --> 00:16:32,440
You've matured quite a bit.

272
00:16:33,980 --> 00:16:37,730
Being a wizard isn't just about being strong.

273
00:16:37,730 --> 00:16:43,470
Anyone could see what you did for the sake 
of your friend today was the right thing.

274
00:16:43,470 --> 00:16:44,930
You should be proud.

275
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:48,110
Right!

276
00:16:49,350 --> 00:16:53,150
Wait... So she's not your 
friend, she's your wife?

277
00:16:53,150 --> 00:16:54,320
No way!

278
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,740
Don't be shy!

279
00:16:55,740 --> 00:16:57,160
She llllikes you!

280
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:01,610
The fog sure is thick, though...

281
00:17:01,610 --> 00:17:04,110
It's especially thick 
during this time of year.

282
00:17:04,110 --> 00:17:05,770
Watch yourself here.

283
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:10,980
When walking in the thick fog, it's 
like walking in another world.

284
00:17:10,980 --> 00:17:12,380
Really?

285
00:17:12,930 --> 00:17:19,240
In the fog before, when I heard you 
searching for me, Natsu, it really made me happy.

286
00:17:20,650 --> 00:17:26,150
Hey... If I disappear again sometime...

287
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:28,810
Will you come and find me, Natsu?

288
00:17:30,570 --> 00:17:32,120
S-Sure...

289
00:17:32,360 --> 00:17:33,870
Promise me?

290
00:17:33,870 --> 00:17:35,310
Yeah, I promise!

291
00:17:36,310 --> 00:17:39,830
Right, Natsu. How about 
we play catch tomorrow?

292
00:17:39,830 --> 00:17:41,980
Sure thing! I ain't gonna lose!

293
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:55,550
But why were you wandering around East 
Forest in the middle of the night?

294
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:59,410
I told you before, remember?

295
00:17:59,410 --> 00:18:00,980
About Igneel...

296
00:18:00,980 --> 00:18:04,900
Right. The red dragon you're looking for.

297
00:18:05,980 --> 00:18:09,600
Lisanna said she found footprints, 
so we went to search.

298
00:18:10,450 --> 00:18:12,980
It was a misunderstanding, though!

299
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,780
Uh? Sorry...

300
00:18:20,010 --> 00:18:24,530
But you really want to meet 
this Igneel fellow, don't you?

301
00:18:25,780 --> 00:18:26,660
Yeah...

302
00:18:31,370 --> 00:18:35,000
As long as you feel that strongly, 
you'll meet him one day.

303
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:36,280
Yeah!

304
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:38,800
Okay, how about we go fishing?

305
00:18:39,070 --> 00:18:42,010
The two of them are like father and son.

306
00:18:42,010 --> 00:18:43,260
Aye!

307
00:19:12,450 --> 00:19:16,060
I wonder if he brought me some rare 
flames from foreign lands or something.

308
00:19:16,060 --> 00:19:17,700
Who knows?

309
00:19:18,170 --> 00:19:19,450
Heya!

310
00:19:19,450 --> 00:19:20,590
Pardon the intrusion!

311
00:19:20,980 --> 00:19:22,430
Oh, you're here.

312
00:19:22,670 --> 00:19:25,160
It's been a long time since I've been here.

313
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:26,850
Three years, right?

314
00:19:27,320 --> 00:19:29,380
So, what's the souvenir?

315
00:19:29,660 --> 00:19:31,190
Put that aside for now.

316
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:34,990
Have things been going well 
between you and Lisanna?

317
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:38,830
Embarrassed, are we?

318
00:19:40,730 --> 00:19:42,570
Lisanna died.

319
00:19:43,510 --> 00:19:44,820
Two years ago.

320
00:19:48,530 --> 00:19:49,930
Really?

321
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:55,060
I see... So that's why Mira...

322
00:19:55,870 --> 00:19:57,750
I'm sorry, Natsu.

323
00:19:58,060 --> 00:20:00,180
If that's what you wanna 
talk about, I'm leaving.

324
00:20:00,180 --> 00:20:01,300
Natsu, hey!

325
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:07,150
Natsu... I met a dragon on this job.

326
00:20:10,180 --> 00:20:14,010
I don't think it's the red one 
that you're searching for.

327
00:20:14,010 --> 00:20:15,190
It was a black dragon.

328
00:20:15,190 --> 00:20:16,560
W-Where?

329
00:20:17,340 --> 00:20:18,590
The holy Mt. Zonia.

330
00:20:18,980 --> 00:20:21,480
And thanks to it, I failed the job.

331
00:20:23,330 --> 00:20:24,630
And what'll you do?

332
00:20:25,490 --> 00:20:29,200
Isn't it obvious? I'll 
ask it where Igneel is.

333
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:35,330
It's gone. It flies around the 
continent, or maybe even the world.

334
00:20:35,330 --> 00:20:39,140
Even so, there might be some clue!

335
00:20:39,140 --> 00:20:41,000
Natsu, take a look at this.

336
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:46,750
It basically all happened in a flash.

337
00:20:47,780 --> 00:20:51,930
My left arm and leg, and 
my internal organs, too...

338
00:20:55,270 --> 00:20:57,850
I don't know what kind of 
guy this Igneel fellow is,

339
00:20:58,110 --> 00:21:01,390
but the black one is an enemy of 
humanity. Of that, there's no doubt.

340
00:21:01,980 --> 00:21:05,540
Plus... A human can't beat it.

341
00:21:06,990 --> 00:21:10,700
The ones who can defeat them 
are the Dragon Slayers!

342
00:21:10,980 --> 00:21:13,870
With my magic, a Black 
Dragon isn't anything...

343
00:21:13,870 --> 00:21:16,700
If you really think that, 
then I won't stop you.

344
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:22,780
Damn it!

345
00:21:23,470 --> 00:21:24,490
Natsu!

346
00:21:24,490 --> 00:21:25,200
Happy.

347
00:21:26,470 --> 00:21:28,760
Give Natsu your support.

348
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:31,630
A human can't beat it.

349
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:33,680
A dragon might be able to.

350
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:37,500
And one day, Natsu will...

351
00:21:45,150 --> 00:21:48,950
There are three Dragon 
Slayers in our guild...

352
00:21:49,740 --> 00:21:53,010
Exactly as Poluchka said.

353
00:21:53,570 --> 00:21:56,510
Fate is trying to make its move.

354
00:21:57,910 --> 00:22:01,190
Damn it! Damn it! Damn it all!

355
00:22:12,830 --> 00:22:15,980
Are you doing well, Igneel?

356
00:22:18,830 --> 00:22:19,890
Dad...

357
00:23:55,790 --> 00:23:57,820
Where'd Gajeel head off to?

358
00:23:57,820 --> 00:24:00,210
I was thinkin' of fighting 
him since I had free time.

359
00:24:00,210 --> 00:24:02,780
Please don't get in fights to kill time.

360
00:24:02,780 --> 00:24:06,330
Anyway, Natsu... The sky looks odd.

361
00:24:06,330 --> 00:24:07,540
Oh, you're right!

362
00:24:07,540 --> 00:24:09,660
We might be in for a shower.

363
00:24:09,660 --> 00:24:11,560
I hope that's all we're in for...

364
00:24:11,560 --> 00:24:14,100
But I've never seen the sky like that!

365
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:16,470
Next time: Earthland.

366
00:24:16,950 --> 00:24:20,090
What else could you mean, more than a shower?

367
00:24:20,330 --> 00:24:21,720
You mean, like a showier shower?

368
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:24,590
You're thinking is even simpler than a cat's!

369
00:24:24,590 --> 00:24:26,820


